<TITLE> 6 die in Sitakunda road crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, July 17 (bdnews24.com)  At least six people died and 15 others were hurt when a bus and a covered van collided on the Dhaka-Chittagong highway in Sitakunda Thursday, police said. Abdul Malek, inspector of Sitakunda highway police, told bdnews24.com that a Sonapur-bound bus collided with the Chittagong-bound covered van in Banshbaria at around 1:30pm leaving four people dead at the scene. Two others died in the Chittagong Medical College Hospital where other injured people were undergoing treatment. The deceased could not be identified immediately, but two of them were women and one a child. Traffic on the highway came to a halt for two hours after the accident. bdnew
